The greateſt Plenty this World can afford to and earthly Heart, is extream Poverty, according to St. Auguſtine, if it be without God; and what-ever Pleaſures or Honours may be enjoyed in this Life, will ſtill end in Miſery and Confuſion, if they advance not the good of the Soul, in order to its endleſs bleſsed Life with God in Heaven; 
                  Ʋbi ſalutis damnum, ibi luerum nulium, ſaith Eucherius; there is no gain to be valued, if therewith our Salvation be endammaged;

 for, if this miſcarries, all is loſt, for an Eternity.
